    • Method Detail

      • actionId

        @Nullable
java.lang.String actionId()
        Action ID - it is the value of the data-action-id ( RichPageWidget.ATTRIBUTE_ACTION_ID ) attribute of the HTML element on which the user clicked.

        Or it is value passed to JavaScript function executeWidgetAction, see PublicJS.executeWidgetAction(Node, boolean, String) for details.

             java.lang.String message)

        Parameters:

      • executeJavaScript

        void executeJavaScript(@Nullable
                       java.lang.String script)
        Calling this method means that the given script should be executed on client side after the action finishes and the optional message(String) is displayed and before replaceWithHtml(String) or refresh(boolean)

      • replaceWithHtml

        void replaceWithHtml(@NotNull
                     java.lang.String html)
        Calling this method means that the content of the widget should be replaced by the given html.

        This is mainly meant for widgets which need to display data based on the action, but do not write any data to persistence. Widgets which write some data should rather use the refresh(boolean) with true, because then the rendering of the widget is executed in a new transaction, which is needed for all indexes to be updated (by committing the write transaction in which the action was executed).

        It usually does not make sense to use this method together with refresh(boolean)

      • refresh

        void refresh(boolean widget)
        Calling this method means that widget or whole page should be refreshed after the action.

        It usually does not make sense to use this method together with replaceWithHtml(String)
        Parameters:
        widget - - true means to refresh the widget, false means to refresh the whole page
